(go-to: "Town Square")

:: Town Square
You awaken in the Town Square of Thornwick, a modest trading town nestled between rolling hills and an ancient forest. The morning sun casts long shadows across the cobblestone plaza. A fountain splashes gently in the center—its water crystal clear—and pigeons peck at scattered breadcrumbs. A street performer tunes a lute nearby, preparing for the day's crowds.

**Status:** Day $day | $time | Health: $health% | Gold: $gold gp | Reputation: $reputation

**Current Quest:** $mainQuest

---

The town awaits your exploration. Where will you venture?

[[→ Market Street]] — The bustling heart of commerce
[[→ North Gate]] — The forest awaits beyond
[[→ Back Alley]] — Dark secrets hidden away
[[→ Town Park]] — Nature's quiet refuge
[[→ Your House]] — The modest home you've rented
[[→ Rest at the fountain]] — Recover some health

---
{
  (if: $questLog's length > 0)[
    **Active Quests:**
    (for: each _q, ...$questLog)[
      • _q
    ]
  ]
}

:: Rest at the fountain
You sit by the fountain, letting the cool mist refresh you. The water feels rejuvenating.

(set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 20))
(set: $time to "Mid-Morning")

As you rest, you notice something glinting beneath the water...

[[Pick it up]] or [[Leave it be]] or [[Return to Town Square]]

:: Pick it up
You reach into the fountain and retrieve a tarnished silver coin. It feels warm to the touch, despite being submerged.

(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Ancient Silver Coin"))
(set: $gold to $gold + 5)

*You've obtained: Ancient Silver Coin and gained 5 gold!*

[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Leave it be
You decide the coin is best left undisturbed.

[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Return to Town Square
(go-to: "Town Square")

:: Market Street
The vibrant energy of Market Street engulfs you. Merchants line the cobbled street, shouting their wares. Colorful flags flutter overhead in the breeze. The aroma of fresh bread, spiced leather, and exotic spices fills your senses. Customers haggle with vendors over prices, and street musicians perform for spare coin.

**Locations:**
• [[Bakery]] — Warmth and the smell of fresh bread
• [[General Shop]] — Tools, supplies, and mysterious trinkets
• [[Suspicious Man]] — A hooded figure watching the crowd
• [[Food Stall]] — Quick meals and information
• [[Return to Town Square]]

---

(set: $time to "Midday")

:: Bakery
You push open the wooden door. A warm gust of air carries the intoxicating smell of fresh bread. The baker, a plump woman named **Elara**, smiles warmly from behind the counter. Her flour-dusted apron tells the story of an early morning's work. Shelves are stacked with golden loaves, pastries, and sweet rolls.

**Elara says:** "Welcome, wanderer. You look like someone new to our town. Can I help you with something?"

(set: $bakerMet to true)
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)

[[Talk about the town]]
[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Buy a bread roll (5 gp)]]
[[Leave the Bakery]]

:: Talk about the town
"Thornwick is a good place," Elara muses, kneading dough. "Most folks here are honest. We get travelers through, merchants, the occasional adventurer. The guard keeps us safe, though there's been talk of strange happenings in the forest lately."

She leans in conspiratorially. "Between you and me, the old man in the park—**Thorne**, we call him—might know more than he lets on. And that suspicious fellow who lingers near the square? Never quite trusted him."

(set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Learn more about the forest and its mysteries"))

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Buy a bread roll (5 gp)]]
[[Leave the Bakery]]

:: Ask about the forest
Elara's expression darkens. "Ah, the forest. It wasn't always dangerous, from what the old-timers say. But something changed about five years ago. Travelers stopped coming from that direction. Strange lights appear some nights. The guard won't go in anymore, and neither will I."

She glances out the window nervously. "If you're thinking of going in there, be careful. Take supplies, and maybe find someone who knows the way."

(unless: $forestUnlocked)[
  (set: $forestUnlocked to true)
]

[[Talk about the town]]
[[Buy a bread roll (5 gp)]]
[[Leave the Bakery]]

:: Buy a bread roll (5 gp)
(if: $gold >= 5)[
  (set: $gold to $gold - 5)
  (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Fresh Bread Roll"))
  (set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 15))
  
  *You've purchased a fresh bread roll. Delicious!*
]
(else)[
  "I'm sorry, friend," Elara says gently. "That'll cost you 5 gold, and you don't have enough."
]

[[Talk about the town]]
[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Leave the Bakery]]

:: Leave the Bakery
You thank Elara and step back out into the bustling Market Street.

[[Market Street]]

:: General Shop
The shop is cramped and cluttered. Shelves overflow with mysterious items: tools of unknown purpose, jars of strange herbs, leather-bound journals, coils of rope, and strange mechanical contraptions. The shopkeeper, a wizened old man named **Garrett**, sits behind the counter, polishing an ornate dagger.

He looks up from his work. "Need something? I've got rare finds if you know what to look for."

**Garrett's Inventory:**
• Rope Coil (10 gp) — Useful for climbing
• Mysterious Map (25 gp) — Shows an "X" marked in the forest
• Healing Potion (15 gp) — Restores 30% health
• Lantern (20 gp) — Essential for dark places
• Strange Key (40 gp) — Purpose unknown

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Browse his wares]]
[[Leave the General Shop]]

:: Ask about the forest
Garrett's weathered face becomes grave. "That forest... it's changed, friend. Five years ago, something happened. A blight, a curse, or perhaps something darker. The forest has its own will now. I've got maps for those brave—or foolish—enough to venture in."

He slides a worn journal across the counter. "Found this in the ruins of a crashed wagon. The explorer who wrote it was heading into the forest. Never came back."

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)

[[Browse his wares]]
[[Leave the General Shop]]

:: Browse his wares
(if: $gold >= 10)[
  "I'll take the [[Rope Coil (10 gp)]] or..." — You can browse different items
]
(else)[
  "I don't have enough gold for much..." — You need more money
]

[[Buy Rope Coil (10 gp)]]
[[Buy Mysterious Map (25 gp)]]
[[Buy Healing Potion (15 gp)]]
[[Buy Lantern (20 gp)]]
[[Leave the General Shop]]

