:: Chat with the vendor
"People come and go through this town," she muses while preparing food. "But lately, fewer are passing through. The forest has people scared. But there's always someone brave or foolish enough to try their luck."

[[Buy Hearty Soup (8 gp)]]
[[Buy Roasted Vegetables (6 gp)]]
[[Buy Pastry (4 gp)]]
[[Return to Market Street]]

:: Return to Market Street
(go-to: "Market Street")

:: North Gate
The North Gate stands imposing and ancient, its wooden frame weathered by centuries of wind and rain. Beyond it, the forest looms like a living wall—trees so tall they seem to touch the sky, their canopy so thick that even midday light struggles to penetrate. The air itself feels different here, cooler and somehow alive with an electric charge.

A grizzled guard in armor stands at attention. His name is **Aldric**, and his weathered face speaks of decades of service. His hand rests on his sword hilt, and his eyes constantly scan the forest.

"Halt," he says, not unkindly. "You look like you're thinking about heading into those woods."

(set: $guardWarned to true)
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Ask why it's dangerous]]
[[Ask if there's a way in]]
[[Try to convince him to let you pass]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Ask about the forest
Aldric takes a long breath. "The forest wasn't always like this. Five years ago, something changed. An old expedition went in, led by a scholar named **Marcus**. He was looking for ancient ruins, an old library supposedly hidden deep within. His team never returned."

He gazes into the darkness. "After that, the forest became... hostile. We've sent patrols, but they all come back traumatized, speaking of shadows that move on their own, and whispers that drive men mad."

(set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Discover what happened to Marcus and his expedition"))

[[Ask why it's dangerous]]
[[Ask if there's a way in]]
[[Try to convince him to let you pass]]

:: Ask why it's dangerous
"Beasts," Aldric says flatly. "Not like normal creatures. These things have an intelligence, a malevolence. We've lost good soldiers to whatever lives in there now."

He looks at you seriously. "The forest has a guardian, or perhaps a curse. I don't know which. But I know that anyone who goes in unprepared doesn't come out."

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Ask if there's a way in]]
[[Try to convince him to let you pass]]

:: Ask if there's a way in
"There is one path," Aldric admits reluctantly. "The old forest road, maintained by the town decades ago. It's overgrown now, but if you follow the stone markers—ancient things carved with symbols—you can find your way deeper in."

He points toward the forest. "Follow the silver stones. They'll take you to the ruin of the old observation tower. From there, if you're lucky, you might make it to the center."

(set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Find the old forest road marked with silver stones"))

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Try to convince him to let you pass]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Try to convince him to let you pass
Aldric watches you for a long moment. "You're brave, I'll give you that. Or foolish. Most likely both."

He steps aside slightly. "I can't stop you—the gates aren't locked. But hear this: the forest will test you. It will show you fears and offer you temptations. Stay true to your purpose, and you might survive. Lose yourself, and you'll become one of the lost souls in there."

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 2)

[[Enter the forest]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Enter the forest
You push open the heavy gates. The forest looms before you, vast and primordial. The air grows cold as shadows engulf you.

(set: $time to "Afternoon")

[[The Ancient Forest Path]]

:: The Ancient Forest Path
You step into the forest. Immediately, the sounds of the town fade. The trees are impossibly old, their bark thick and gnarled like the skin of ancient creatures. Moss and fungus cover rotting logs. The canopy is so thick that midday light becomes twilight.

You notice the forest road—barely visible beneath centuries of overgrowth—and the first silver stone, carved with mysterious symbols that seem to pulse faintly with an inner light.

As you walk, you hear sounds. Whispers on the wind. The crunch of unseen footsteps. The distant cry of something large and unseen.

The forest is testing you.

[[Follow the silver stone markers]] — The safe path
[[Venture off the path]] — The mysterious route
[[Rest and prepare]] — Gather your strength
[[Return to town]] — Safety awaits

:: Follow the silver stone markers
(set: $health to $health - 10)

You follow the silver stones, each one leading deeper into the forest. The markers are your guide, your anchor against the madness of this place.

After hours of walking, you discover something extraordinary—the old observation tower, covered in vines and crumbling with age. But behind it, you see something else: an ancient archway of stone, clearly not natural, clearly not accidental.

**You've found the Gateway to the Old Ruins.**

[[Investigate the archway]]
[[Rest at the tower]]
[[Return to town]]

:: Investigate the archway
You approach the archway cautiously. It's carved with the same symbols as the silver stones, but far more intricate. In the center, there's a lock... but no keyhole you can see.

Suddenly, you remember the Ancient Silver Coin you found in the fountain. You pull it out, and it glows with the same light as the stones.

(if: "Ancient Silver Coin" is in $inventory)[
  The coin slides perfectly into a hidden slot in the archway. The stone glows brilliantly, and with a deep rumble, the archway opens, revealing a passage into the earth below.
  
  **You've unlocked the passage to the Ancient Library!**
  (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Explore the Ancient Library"))
  (set: $completedQuests to $completedQuests + (a: "Opened the Gateway to the Old Ruins"))
  
  [[Enter the Library]]
]
(else)[
  Without the key, the archway remains sealed. You'll need to find something to unlock it.
  
  [[Rest at the tower]]
  [[Return to town]]
]

:: Enter the Library
(set: $time to "Evening")
(set: $health to $health - 10)

You descend into darkness. Your footsteps echo on ancient stone. The air grows warmer, and a faint blue light emanates from within.

You emerge into a vast underground chamber. Books line endless shelves. At the center stands a stone pedestal, and upon it rests a scroll of incredible age. Behind the pedestal, you see a skeleton—the remains of **Marcus**, the missing scholar.

Next to the skeleton is a journal, its pages filled with frantic notes about "the curse," "the stone's power," and "the ritual that went wrong."

[[Read Marcus's Journal]]
[[Take the ancient scroll]]
[[Pay respects and leave]]

:: Read Marcus's Journal
You carefully open the journal. The entries tell a tragic story:

*"Day 1: We've found the library! It's magnificent. The knowledge here could change everything."*

*"Day 7: We've found something... a stone, ancient beyond measure. It pulses with power."*

*"Day 12: Marcus attempted to use the stone to unlock deeper secrets. Something went wrong. The forest itself seems to have awakened. My companions are... changing."*

*"Day 15: I'm the only one left. The stone's power is spreading. Marcus is gone, consumed by the light. I can't leave—the forest won't let me. This journal will be my legacy."*

The final entry is barely legible, as if written by trembling hands.

(set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Discover the truth about the curse"))
(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Marcus's Journal"))
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 3)

[[Take the ancient scroll]]
[[Return to town with the knowledge]]

:: Take the ancient scroll
You carefully lift the scroll from the pedestal. It's warm to the touch, and ancient symbols glow softly on its surface. The scroll describes an ancient ritual—a way to bind the curse and restore the forest to peace.

(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Scroll of Unbinding"))
(set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Perform the Unbinding Ritual to free the forest"))
(set: $completedQuests to $completedQuests + (a: "Discovered the truth in the Ancient Library"))

[[Return to town with the knowledge]]
[[Perform the ritual here]]

:: Perform the ritual here
(set: $health to $health - 20)

You unfurl the scroll and begin to read the ancient words aloud. Your voice echoes through the chamber. The stone beneath your feet begins to glow, brighter and brighter, until light fills the entire cavern.

Reality seems to shimmer. The curse unravels. The forest screams, a sound like a thousand voices crying out in pain and then, finally, relief.

When the light fades, silence returns. The curse is broken.

(set: $completedQuests to $completedQuests + (a: "Performed the Unbinding Ritual"))
(set: $questLog to $questLog - (a: "Perform the Unbinding Ritual to free the forest"))
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 10)

You've become a hero.

[[Return to town]]

:: Return to town with the knowledge
The forest path seems easier now, as if it's guiding you back. The ancient corruption feels diminished.

You emerge from the forest as dusk falls, carrying knowledge that could save your town.

(go-to: "Town Square")

:: Pay respects and leave
You bow respectfully before Marcus's remains, grateful for his sacrifice and the knowledge he paid for with his life.

(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Marcus's Journal"))

[[Return to town]]

:: Return to town
(go-to: "Town Square")

:: Rest at the tower
You make camp at the tower, gathering your strength for what comes next.

(set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 30))
(set: $time to "Night")

In the morning, you'll decide what to do.

[[Investigate the archway]]
[[Return to town]]

:: Venture off the path
(set: $health to $health - 20)

You leave the marked path, following your instincts deeper into the forest. Almost immediately, you sense you've made a mistake.

The trees close in. The shadows deepen. You hear whispers, and you see shapes moving in the darkness—shapes that shouldn't exist.

After what feels like hours of wandering, you stumble into a clearing where a massive stone statue stands—ancient and covered in moss. At its base, you find something glinting: a key made of crystal.

[[Take the key]]
[[Leave the clearing and find the path]]

:: Take the key
(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Crystal Key"))
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 2)

The moment you touch it, you understand—this key belongs to something ancient, something important.

[[Find the path back]]

:: Find the path back
(set: $health to $health - 10)

You manage to find your way back to the silver stone markers.

[[Follow the silver stone markers]]

:: Leave the clearing and find the path
(set: $health to $health - 5)

You carefully back away from the statue and find your way back to the silver stones.

[[Follow the silver stone markers]]

:: Back Alley
The alley is narrow and dark, squeezed between two old buildings. Water drips from a broken gutter, echoing off wet cobblestones. The smell is unpleasant—a mixture of rotting garbage and something chemical you can't quite identify.

But there's also something intriguing. A door, painted a deep green, stands slightly ajar. Light spills from within.

[[Investigate the sound]]
[[Knock on the green door]]
[[Search the trash]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Investigate the sound
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)

You follow the dripping sound and discover it's coming from a broken pipe. As you examine it, you notice something wedged behind it—a small leather pouch containing 15 gold and a note:

*"For whoever finds this. I'm sorry for what I've done. The curse in the forest... I helped cause it. Forgive me. —M"*

(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Mysterious Note"))
(set: $gold to $gold + 15)
(set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Discover who left this note and what they meant"))

[[Knock on the green door]]
[[Search the trash]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Knock on the green door
The door opens wider, revealing a dimly lit room filled with curiosities. Behind a cluttered desk sits an elderly woman with sharp eyes.

"Come in, come in," she says. "I've been expecting someone."

She introduces herself as **Iris**, a hedge witch and keeper of forgotten knowledge.

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 2)

[[Ask what she knows about the forest]]
[[Ask what she is]]
[[Leave]]

:: Ask what she knows about the forest
"The forest," Iris says solemnly, "is cursed by ambition and greed. A scholar tried to use ancient power, not understanding what he was doing. The forest punished him for it. But the curse can be broken."

She slides a small vial across her desk. "This is a potion. It will help you see the truth in the forest, to understand what needs to be done."

(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Iris's Truth Potion"))
(set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Use Iris's potion to see the truth in the forest"))

[[Ask what she is]]
[[Leave]]

:: Ask what she is
"I am someone who remembers," Iris says mysteriously. "I remember when the forest was beautiful. When the curse didn't exist. I've been waiting for someone brave enough to undo what was done. Perhaps that someone is you."

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)

[[Ask what she knows about the forest]]
[[Leave]]

:: Leave
You step back out into the alley.

[[Back Alley]]

:: Search the trash
(set: $health to $health - 5)

You search through refuse and garbage. Mostly you find nothing, but in an old crate, you discover a rusted key and a broken compass.

(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Rusted Key"))
(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Broken Compass"))

[[Knock on the green door]]
[[Investigate the sound]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Town Park
The park is a sanctuary of peace within the bustling town. Ancient oaks provide shade, and benches line the walking paths. A small pond reflects the sky, and wildflowers bloom in carefully tended gardens. Few people are present—mostly those seeking quiet.

Sitting on a weathered bench, watching the water, is an elderly man. His eyes seem to contain centuries of wisdom.

[[Sit on the bench]]
[[Talk to the old man]]
[[Explore the park]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Sit on the bench
You sit down quietly, letting the peace of the park wash over you.

(set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 15))

After a while, the old man speaks. "It's a good place for thinking, isn't it?"

[[Talk to the old man]]

:: Talk to the old man
The old man introduces himself as **Thorne**, and he claims to be over a hundred years old. His mind, however, is sharp.

"I remember when the forest was young," he says. "When it was beautiful and safe. I've watched it change, watched it darken. I think something in its heart has been corrupted, and I think you might be the one to fix it."

(set: $oldManMet to true)
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 2)

He gives you a small carved token. "When you're in the deepest part of the forest, hold this. It might help you find what you're looking for."

(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Thorne's Token"))

[[Ask about the forest's history]]
[[Ask how he knows about you]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Ask about the forest's history
"Five hundred years ago," Thorne begins, "the forest was a paradise. Then came the ambition of men. Scholars and mages tried to unlock its secrets. They found something—an ancient artifact of great power—and they wanted to use it."

He pauses, lost in memory. "The forest rejected them. It awakened defenses. Most of the explorers died. The few who survived sealed themselves away and never spoke of it again. But the corruption spread, year by year, until five years ago, when a new attempt was made..."

[[Ask how he knows about you]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Ask how he knows about you
Thorne smiles. "I know because I've lived long enough to recognize the signs. When someone new arrives in town, I can feel it. And when that someone carries the weight of destiny, I can see it in their eyes. You're here for a reason, whether you know it yet or not."

[[Ask about the forest's history]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Explore the park
You wander through the park's quiet paths, finding small surprises—a hidden fountain, a grove of ancient trees, a stone monument covered in names.

The names, you realize, are those of people lost to the forest over centuries.

(set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Understand why so many have been lost to the forest"))

[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Your House
Your small rented home is modest but comfortable. It's a cottage with a small garden out front, a fireplace, and simple furnishings. A window overlooks the town.

(set: $houseExplored to true)

What will you do here?

[[Look out the window]]
[[Rest on the bed]]
[[Examine your belongings]]
[[Leave]]

:: Look out the window
You gaze out over the town of Thornwick, watching the sunset. From here, you can see the market, the north gate, and in the distance, the dark mass of the forest.

It seems to be watching you back.

[[Rest on the bed]]
[[Leave]]

